response.headerFullLocation: Downtown San Francisco-Union Square, San Francisco

tips.text: Mikkeller Bar just opened a secret private beer room in the basement (use these not-at-all-scary stairs) devoted entirely to sours.
Fried Chicken w/ Mac n Cheese = AMAZING.
Butter chicken!!! One of the best sauces I've ever tried, EVER. The owner is always there & is a cool guy.
Seekers of authentic Thai flavor will like Kin Khao. Expect housemade curry pastes and chili jam and unusual offerings like the saeng-wah salad, a ceviche-like shrimp dish over ground catfish.
Best Thai rest. In SF;)
be careful downstairs. it seems like a scene out of the godfather.

You know they have like sandwiches. Usually a daily deal. Only two tables so that sucks. Fast friendly service every time  and they have to put up with a lot.
